    "body": "### Problem\n\nUpdated to latest commit after few days off.\nNow, running local git commands in a root where the user.name is not cached results in a command failure.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n> NOTE: must be a repo where user.name is not set and must be typed from stdin.\n\n```\nnvim --clean\n:! git push\n```\n\nWill get:\n\n<img width=\"1320\" height=\"252\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a9162fe3-30e5-4cb9-bce0-b3e0ee4fe437\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCommand running, and NVim's command line waiting for user input.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-2847 g7a27c5b0c8\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, 8.2\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux 6.8.0-107-generic\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGNOME terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
